    "body": "### Problem\n\n`showmode` in `terminal_enter` may cause an `os_breakcheck` that causes `term_settermprop` to hide the cursor via `ui_busy_start`, then sets `term->cursor.visible = false`. (`showmode` -> `skip_showmode` -> `char_avail` -> `vpeekc` -> `loop_poll_events` -> ... -> `term_settermprop`)\n\nIf this happens, the `if (!s->term->cursor.visible)` check in `terminal_enter` will cause `ui_busy_start` to be called _again_, incrementing `busy` an extra time; this can result in `busy` being left with a non-zero value after leaving terminal mode, causing the cursor to remain invisible.  \n\nHappens after the terminal cursor changes in #31562 (0dd933265ff).  \nAppears to be the cause of ibhagwan/fzf-lua#1827.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSource the following with `--clean` (not at startup):\n\n```lua\nvim.cmd.new()\n-- Not using chansend here; want terminal_receive to happen via terminal_start -> showmode -> ... -> vpeekc\nvim.fn.jobstart([[echo -e \"\\e[?25l\"]], {term = true})\nvim.api.nvim__redraw({valid = false})\n\nvim.cmd.startinsert()\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"TermClose\", {\n  once = true,\n  callback = function(args)\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(args.buf, {force = true})\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nNotice that the cursor remains hidden; `busy` remains non-zero.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMatching number of `busy_stop` to `busy_start` events; cursor does not remain hidden.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0a0f536\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5a (in ghostty b975f1e)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
